-8"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Inge9_8-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Inge9_8-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Inge9_8-2"><span class="mw-linkback-text">3 </span></a><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Inge9_8-3"><span class="mw-linkback-text">4 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Inge9-8" class="mw-reference-text">Inge (1990), 9</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Mulhern78ff-9" id="cite_note-Mulhern78ff-9"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Mulhern78ff_9-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-Mulhern78ff_9-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Mulhern78ff-9" class="mw-reference-text">Mulhern (1991), 79</span></li><li about="#cite_note-10" id="cite_note-10"><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-10" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-10" class="mw-reference-text">Adolphson (2007), 111</span></li><li about="#cite_note-11" id="cite_note-11"><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-11" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-11" class="mw-reference-text">Seven women were named in the entry, with the actual names of four women known. Of the remaining three women, one was not a Fujiwara, one held a high rank and therefore had to be older, leaving the possibility that the third, Fujiwara no Takako, was Murasaki. See Tsunoda (1963), 1–27</span></li><li about="#cite_note-12" id="cite_note-12"><a href="./Murasaki_Shikibu#cite_ref-12" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-12" class="mw-reference-text">Ueno (2009), 254</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Shirane218-13" id="cite_note-Shirane218-13"><sp